A tremor shook Mount St. Helens for 25 minutes early Sunday,prompting scientists to warn of an imminent eruption two days afterthe volcano came back to life.
Government scientists raised the alert level for Mount St. Helensafter its second steam eruption in two days was followed by apowerful tremor.
Lots of people here remember well how racked with fear they were inthe weeks and days leading up to the 1980 eruption of Mount St.Helens, the volcano that rained utter havoc from 30 miles away onthis tiny town.
